{/* Project 1 */} } >

Handwriting comparison using Linear Regression, Logistic Regression and Neural Network.

PROJECT DETAILS Description: The goal of this project is to find similarities between hand written copies of two different writers by using CEDAR as data source. Features:
  • Human Observed features: Features entered by human document examiners manually
  • GSC features: Features extracted using Gradient Structural Concavity (GSC) algorithm.
Models:
  • Linear Regression using Stochastic Gradient Descent.
  • Logistic Regression using Stochastic Gradient descent.
  • Neural networks.
Tech used:
  • Python
  • TensorFlow
  • Keras
  • Jupyter Notebook
{/* Project 2 */} } >

Classifiers

PROJECT DETAILS Description: The goal of this project to implement the Ensemble Learning process on MNIST dataset. Features:
  • MNIST Dataset
  • USPS Dataset
Models:
  • Logistic Regression using Softmax.
  • Dense Neural networks[DNN].
  • Convoluted Neural netwotk [CNN].
  • Random Forest.
  • Support Vector Machine [SVM].
Tech used:
  • Python
  • TensorFlow
  • Keras
  • Jupyter Notebook
